	type : "Newsletter", 		// Article, newsletter, event, tv
	
	title : "Check it out: Special Debate Workshop &#038; Mid-Autumn Festival at Point Avenue",		// 뉴스 제목
	
	thumbnail : {		
		excerpt : "<p>Register NOW for the special upcoming events at Point Avenue!  *Our event implement strict measure to ensure attendances and students’ safety in the spread of COVID-19 pandemic 1/ Special Debate Workshop: Speak Up for What You Believe In Instructor: Ms. Hyewon Rho Head of Debate Program &#8211; Point Avenue Head Coach of Team Vietnam for [&hellip;]</p>",	// 섬네일에 보일 내용
		imageUrl : "https://www.pointavenue.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Debate-workshop.jpg"	// 섬네일 이미지 URL
	}
	
	date: "2020-09-11T11:26:03",
	lang : "en",		// 언어속성
	newsletter : {
		contents : "<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Register <strong>NOW</strong> for the special upcoming events at Point Avenue! </span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">*</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our event implement strict measure to ensure attendances and students’ safety in the spread of COVID-19 pandemic</span></i></p> <p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/773362370081849/?acontext=%7B%22event_action_history%22%3A[%7B%22mechanism%22%3A%22search_results%22%2C%22surface%22%3A%22search%22%7D]%7D"><b>1/ Special Debate Workshop: Speak Up for What You Believe In</b></a></p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2545" src="https://www.pointavenue.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Debate-workshop.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="859" /></p> <p><b>Instructor: Ms. Hyewon Rho</b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Head of Debate Program &#8211; Point Avenue</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Head Coach of Team Vietnam for World Schools Debating Championships (WSDC) 2020</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Co-Coach of Team Korea for World Schools Debating Championships (WSDC) 2014-2019</span></li> </ul> <p><b>Workshop 1: </b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Time: 10:00 &#8211; 12:00, Saturday, September 12</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Place: Point Avenue &#8211; Long Bien Office: No. 60 Chu Huy Man St., Phuc Dong Ward, Long Bien Dist., Hanoi</span></li> </ul> <p><b>Workshop 2: </b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Time: 17:00 &#8211; 19:00, Thursday, September 17</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Location: Point Avenue &#8211; Cau Giay Office: 2nd Floor, CT1 Yen Hoa Park View, No. 3 Vu Pham Ham St., Cau Giay Dist., Hanoi</span></li> </ul> <p><b>Registration Fee (lunch/dinner included):</b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">100,000 VND for students who is studying or used to study at Point Avenue</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">300,000 VND for non Point Avenue students</span></li> </ul> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This special workshop will introduce brainstorming methods used in competitive debating. Students will be able to apply their new skill in analyzing complex issues and creating effective solutions. The workshop will be led by Ms. Hyewon Rho, the Head of Debate Programs and Point Avenue and the Head Coach of Team Vietnam for World Schools Debating Championships.</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The aim will be to provide the young &amp; talented teens the opportunity to develop 21st century skills of critical thinking, collaboration, communication, and creativity through debate.</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The workshop will be in English, and is limited to a maximum of 12 students. Parents &amp; students please register at: </span><a href="https://bit.ly/PA-SpecialDebateWorkshop2020?fbclid=IwAR0t900zCieQ7gmLMbzWeL1A90J-xnBFZUmNlOL7lWZOBcw-rSp3DkUUeL0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">http://bit.ly/PA-SpecialDebateWorkshop2020</span></a></p> <p><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/774804896587999?acontext=%7B%22event_action_history%22%3A[%7B%22mechanism%22%3A%22search_results%22%2C%22surface%22%3A%22search%22%7D]%7D">2/ Point Avenue Mid-Autumn Festival Community Day</a></strong></p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2544" src="https://www.pointavenue.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mid-autumn-point-avenue.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="860" /></p> <p><b>Event 1: </b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Time: 9:30 &#8211; 11:30, Sunday, September 13</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Location: Point Avenue Long Bien: 60 Chu Huy Man St., Sai Dong New Urban Area, Phuc Dong, Long Bien</span></li> </ul> <p><b>Event 2</b></p> <ul> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Time: 9:30 &#8211; 11:30, Sunday, September 20</span></li> <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Location: Point Avenue Cau Giay: 2nd floor, Yen Hoa Park View CT1 Building, 3 Vu Pham Ham St., Yen Hoa, Cau Giay</span></li> </ul> <p><b>Guest speaker: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dr. Myles Lynch, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ph.D. from </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">the University of New Hampshire</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Continuing the Apollo-11 dream of space exploration 50 years ago, this Mid-Autumn Festival, the &#8220;Journey to the Moon&#8221; with the spacecraft &#8220;SPACE &#8211; PA&#8221; did create various challenges and activities for the whole family on this trip. </span></p> <p><b>Hands-on activities for children aged 5-9 years old: </b></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">🤖 Coding Challenge through space with Dash the robot</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">🌙 Solve Engineering Puzzles to build a Tower to the Moon</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">🏮 Explore the topic of Environment and Recycling by making lanterns</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">🎭 Unleash your creativity by decorating cardboard masks</span></p> <p><b>Parent Workshop: &#8220;How to nurture your child&#8217;s creativity?&#8221; </b></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This workshop will be hosted by Dr. Myles Lync, who primarily works in Education with a focus on the intersection of creativity and motivation among young children in various work and school contexts. Dr. Myles Lynch also has 7 publications in international peer-reviewed academic journals and has taught University level courses with a focus on natural resource management, outdoor education, and educational psychology.</span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Register for free tickets now at: </span><a href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2FPA-MidAutumnFestival2020%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR0t900zCieQ7gmLMbzWeL1A90J-xnBFZUmNlOL7lWZOBcw-rSp3DkUUeL0&amp;h=AT2BaLvtuPfrGDngrCFGohaGgGe4lYZnZFUmwXBjWzKitna8KIlh9AEOl9E3VCU75MuSV3wKregxsrYQhnIDgehQlFx2qV84s6VP2J9tncXilCZLsIsFLTHdokZj3AyJFmilrd-Vog"><span style="font-weight: 400;">http://bit.ly/PA-MidAutumnFestival2020</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></p> <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We can&#8217;t wait to welcome you to Point Avenue! </span></p>",		// 뉴스레터 내용, 
	}
},
	
